@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="container-fluid p-0">
    <div
        class="text-center">
        <div class="text-center px-3">
            <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p class="lead mt-3">Your data matters. Here’s how we handle it responsibly.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Privacy Policy Section -->
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>
            We, PET Group, are committed to respecting and protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines how we
            collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you interact with our services or platforms.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Controllers of Personal Information</h2>
        <p>
            PET Group, affiliated with SDU, oversees the management of personal data collected via our projects and
            platforms. Our headquarters are based at Alsion.
        </p>

        <h2>2. What Personal Information We Collect</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Information you provide:</strong> Name, email address, academic details, and other voluntarily
                submitted data.</li>
            <li><strong>Automatically collected:</strong> Usage data, cookies, IP address, and device information.</li>
            <li><strong>Third-party sources:</strong> Data from external services like payment processors or analytics
                providers (if applicable).</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>To provide, maintain, and improve our services.</li>
            <li>To comply with institutional and legal requirements.</li>
            <li>For academic research and development purposes.</li>
            <li>For personalization and recommendations.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Cookies and Identifiers</h2>
        <p>
            PET Group uses cookies to enhance functionality and improve user experience. You can manage your preferences
            via your browser settings or through our cookie management tool.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Data Sharing</h2>
        <p>
            We do not sell your data. We, PET Group, share information only with trusted institutional partners or
            service providers under strict confidentiality agreements, where necessary.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
            You have the right to access, update, or request the deletion of your personal data. For assistance, please
            contact our Project Lead at Alsion.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Security Measures</h2>
        <p>
            We prioritize data security using encryption, secure servers, and strict access controls. Our protocols
            comply with institutional and industry standards.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
            For privacy-related inquiries, please reach out to us at Alsion.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Updates to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
            This policy may be updated periodically to reflect changes in our practices. Please revisit this page for
            the latest version.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

